Translation:

Ljusdal, Gävleborg. 1. Got married in 1916 to Beda Swebilius. Graduated from Mogarelius Examination Institute in Linköping in 1905, Bachelor of Arts in Uppsala in 1908, probationary year in Lund in 1911. Extra teacher in Linköping in 1908, 1909-1910, and 1912-1913, substitute lecturer in Gävle in 1912, assistant teacher in Västerås in 1913, assistant in mathematics and physics at Norrköping high school since 1920. Administrative assistant to the principal in Västerås from 1918 to 1920. Representative for school board at the secondary school in Söderköping from 1924 to 1926, Katrineholm from 1927 to 1928, Solbacka from 1931 to 1933. Member of the examination board for private schools in Örebro in 1928, Norrköping in 1929. Received the Royal Order of Vasa.
